Dual-license notice for tools/shortcodes-generator/.

This tool is a derivative work of the theme's shortcode family. The
tooling code itself (the dev server, the YAML schema, the form widgets,
the generator logic, the rendered preview, and the README) is licensed
under GPL-2.0-or-later — same as the theme's skin chrome at
LICENSE in the repo root.

The per-shortcode field lists under data/*.yaml mirror the upstream
MediaWiki `Template:Infobox <topic>` parameter names (snake_case keys
like `birth_date`, `nationality`, `population_total`). The parameter
*names* are facts (MediaWiki convention) and are not copyrightable.
The accompanying *conditionals* and *worked examples* are original
prose authored for this theme and are released under GPL-2.0-or-later
alongside the code. The infobox-content license statement in
docs/SHORTCODES.md §0 — CC BY-SA 4.0 for per-topic conditional logic
ported from Wikipedia — applies to the corresponding rendered infobox
content, not to the YAML field lists here. The tool merely emits the
parameter names; it does not transclude any Wikipedia content.

Wikipedia contributors are the joint authors of the parameter-naming
convention this tool reuses; their upstream template text is licensed
CC BY-SA 4.0. Attribution is recorded per-shortcode in the `upstream:`
field of each data/<slug>.yaml and in docs/SHORTCODES.md §11.

